<p>Swift (from the book 《iOS Animations by Tutorials:Chapter 12》 released by <a href="http://www.raywenderlich.com/" rel="nofollow">http://www.raywenderlich.com/</a>):</p>  <pre><code>let photoLayer = CALayer()  @IBInspectable   var image: UIImage! {     didSet {       photoLayer.contents = image.CGImage     } } </code></pre>  <p>How can I implement the above syntax in objective-c? I know only to set the property of photoLayer and image like below:</p>  <pre><code>@property (strong, nonatomic) CALayer *photoLayer; @property (strong, nonatomic) IBInspectable UIImage *image; </code></pre>  <p>But i do not know how to implement <code>didset{...}</code> parts using objective-c syntax, please help!</p>